Program: Free Thinking
Title: Free Thinking at Uproot Festival
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08jb1w4
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 6 Apr 2017
Island city mentality or gateway to the world? Hull-based crime writer and former journalist David Mark, poet Adelle Stripe and Slung Low artistic director Alan Lane join Matthew Sweet to debate Hull's links with the wider world, while playwright Esther Wilson suggest what residents can learn from another port city which has been City of Culture - Liverpool. Recorded with an audience at Hull Truck Theatre as part of Radio 3's Uproot festival for Hull 2017. Producer: Torquil MacLeod. Show less